      • ValidateOrder

        public static boolean ValidateOrder​(Player p_player,
                                    String p_sourceCountryId,
                                    String p_targetCountryId,
                                    String p_armiesToAirlift)
        The function "ValidateOrder" checks if a player can perform an airlift order by validating the source and target countries, as well as the number of armies to airlift.
        Parameters:
        p_player - The player object representing the player who is initiating the order.
        p_sourceCountryId - The ID of the country from which the player wants to airlift armies.
        p_targetCountryId - The target country ID is a string that represents the ID of the country where the player wants to airlift their armies to.
        p_armiesToAirlift - The parameter "p_armiesToAirlift" represents the number of armies that the player wants to airlift from the source country to the target country.
        Returns:
        The method is returning a boolean value.

      • GetCountryForAirlift

        public static Country GetCountryForAirlift​(Player p_player,
                                           String p_countryId)
        Retrieves the country intended for an airlift based on the player and country ID. If the country ID is null or an error occurs during processing, it logs an appropriate message.
        Parameters:
        p_player - The player for whom the country is being fetched.
        p_countryId - The ID of the country to be retrieved.
        Returns:
        The Country intended for airlift; returns null if the country ID is null or not found.
